The paper deals with the maximum clique problem on a specific family of graphs, namely inductive k-independent graphs and their subclass, k-degenerate graphs. These are graph-theoretic concepts and hence the paper is likely to belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. The paper also involves approximation algorithms and fixed parameter tractability, which are topics in theoretical computer science, making cs.CC (Computational Complexity) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper discusses some structural properties of inductive k-independent graphs, which could fall under the cs.GT (Graph Theory) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on algorithms and optimization suggests that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
